mages</figcaption></figure><p>这些利润很可能得益于流媒体服务<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announce-new-premium-price-hike-for-the-us-3762105">在 2024 年 6 月上旬提高了大部分现有计划的价格。</a>此外， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announces-cut-of-1500-jobs-with-17-per-cent-of-workforce-facing-axe-3552871">Spotify 决定在 2023 年底削减 17% 的员工以节省成本，</a>这可能也有助于他们的利润增加。这一决定是在之前实施的一项计划之后做出的<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-to-cut-six-per-cent-of-workforce-3385265">，该计划旨在于 2023 年初再裁员 6%，</a>以提高“速度”。</p><p>除了涨价和裁员之外，利润很可能还受益于流媒体服务<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-has-now-officially-demonetised-all-songs-with-less-than-1000-streams-3614010">正式取消平台上所有流媒体量不足 1000 首的歌曲</a>。</p><p>该政策于4月1日推出，但<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-confirm-songs-now-need-at-least-1000-streams-to-earn-royalties-3546548">平台已经筹划了一段时间</a>。它很快就受到批评，因为<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announce-profit-and-millions-more-subscribers-but-also-royalty-cuts-to-less-popular-tracks-3521362">它让艺术家更难从他们的音乐中获得版税，并限制了想要闯入音乐行业的新艺术家</a>。</p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kate-nash">凯特·纳什 (Kate Nash)</a>最近在她的<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kate-nash-and-her-bum-on-the-back-of-a-fire-truck-take-to-livenation-offices-to-protest-3816821">“屁股坐在消防车后面”抗议活动中强调了流媒体版权费过低的问题，当时她前往 Spotify 伦敦办事处</a>，通过扩音器说道：“艺术家每场直播的报酬为 0.003 便士，而 [Spotify]平台上 80% 的音乐被非货币化。股东们总共套现了超过 4.19 亿美元。”</p><p>最近，一个<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-unwrapped-parody-site-taken-down-under-legal-threat-after-claiming-what-artists-really-earned-from-streams-in-2024-3819279">模仿 Spotify Wrapped 的网站在 Spotify 法律团队的要求下被关闭。</a>该网站名为“ <a href="https://www.spotifyunwrapped.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Spotify Unwrapped</a> ”，重点介绍了艺术家从该平台获得的低收入。 </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/C_YCjHmRloO/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-ra